msgctxt "sn36.18:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 36 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 36 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.18:0.2"
msgid "2. Rahogatavagga "
msgstr "2. In Private "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 18. Dutiyasambahulasutta → dutiyaaṭṭhakasuttaṃ (bj) | aṭṭhaka 2 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn36.18:0.3"
msgid "18. Dutiyasambahulasutta "
msgstr "18. With Several Mendicants (2nd) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.223, sc1
msgctxt "sn36.18:1.1"
msgid "Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu … pe … "
msgstr "Then several mendicants went up to the Buddha … "

msgctxt "sn36.18:1.2"
msgid "ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said to them: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.18:1.3"
msgid "“katamā nu kho, bhikkhave, vedanā, katamo vedanāsamudayo, katamo vedanānirodho, katamā vedanānirodhagāminī paṭipadā? "
msgstr "“Mendicants, what is feeling? What’s the origin of feeling? What’s the cessation of feeling? What’s the practice that leads to the cessation of feeling? "

msgctxt "sn36.18:1.4"
msgid "Ko vedanāya assādo, ko ādīnavo, kiṃ nissaraṇan”ti? "
msgstr "And what is feeling’s gratification, drawback, and escape?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.18:1.5"
msgid "“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe …” "
msgstr "“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. …” "

# NOTE: Glitch in punctuation here, I have corrected it.
#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.18:1.6"
msgid "“tisso imā, bhikkhave, vedanā—"
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these three feelings: "

msgctxt "sn36.18:1.7"
msgid "sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā, adukkhamasukhā vedanā—"
msgstr "pleasant, painful, and neutral. "

msgctxt "sn36.18:1.8"
msgid "imā vuccanti, bhikkhave, vedanā … pe … phassasamudayā … pe …. "
msgstr "These are called feeling. …” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.18:1.9"
msgid "(Yathā purimasuttante, tathā vitthāretabbo.) "
msgstr "(This should be told in full as in the previous discourse.) "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn36.18:1.10"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

